'''Deniz Undav''' ({{IPA|de|ˈdɛnɪs ˈʊndaːf|-|}}; born 19 July 1996) is a German professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{German football updater|Stuttgart}} club [[VfB Stuttgart]] and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]].

==Club career==
===Early career (2002–2020)===
Undav, who grew up in [[Achim]], played for TSV Achim before joining the youth department of [[SV Werder Bremen|Werder Bremen]], in which he was released after five years due to his lack of height. Later on, he joined SC Weyhe, then [[TSV Havelse]] where he made his senior debut during the [[2014–15 Regionalliga]]. He later played for [[Eintracht Braunschweig II]], followed by [[SV Meppen]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.sport1.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/2023/08/bundesliga-die-aussergewohnliche-karriere-des-deniz-undav-uber-stuttgart-zur-em |title=Stuttgarts neuer Hoffnungsträger |publisher=Sport1 |language=de |date=4 August 2023 |access-date=29 January 2024 |archive-date=29 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240129192828/https://www.sport1.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/2023/08/bundesliga-die-aussergewohnliche-karriere-des-deniz-undav-uber-stuttgart-zur-em |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Union Saint-Gilloise (2020–2022)===
[[File:RC Lens - Union-Saint-Gilloise (05-08-2020) 46.jpg|thumb|upright|Undav with [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union SG]] in 2020]]
In April 2020, it was announced Undav would leave [[3. Liga]] club SV Meppen at the end of the 2019–20 season. With his Meppen contract running out, he would join [[Belgian First Division B]] side [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union Saint-Gilloise]] on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |title=SV Meppen verliert Topstürmer Undav |url=https://www.ndr.de/sport/fussball/3-Liga-SV-Meppen-verliert-Topstuermer-Undav,meppen1748.html |website=NDR.de |accessdate=8 April 2020 |language=German |date=7 April 2020 |archive-date=14 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220314054635/https://www.ndr.de/sport/fussball/3-Liga-SV-Meppen-verliert-Topstuermer-Undav,meppen1748.html |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Meppen enttäuscht: Top-Torjäger Undav geht nach Belgien |url=https://www.kicker.de/meppen_enttaeuscht_top_torjaeger_undav_geht_nach_belgien-773549/artikel |website=kicker |access-date=8 April 2020 |language=German |date=7 April 2020 |archive-date=8 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241108233131/https://www.kicker.de/meppen_enttaeuscht_top_torjaeger_undav_geht_nach_belgien-773549/artikel |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 13 March 2021, Undav won the championship with [[Royale Union Saint-Gilloise|Union Saint-Gilloise]] in the [[Belgian First Division B]] ending his season on 17 goals in 26 games.

On the 15th matchday in the [[2021–22 Belgian First Division A]] season Undav scored, for the first time in his career, a quadruple away at [[K.V. Oostende]] in the 7–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/union-saint-gilloise/deniz-undav-a-realise-l-un-de-ses-plus-gros-matches-avec-l-union-juste-incroyable-619ab5b89978e25ff0a2d666 |title=Deniz Undav a réalisé l'un de ses plus gros matches avec l'Union |website=dhnet.be |language=fr |date=22 November 2021 |access-date=24 November 2021 |archive-date=24 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211124141940/https://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1a/union-saint-gilloise/deniz-undav-a-realise-l-un-de-ses-plus-gros-matches-avec-l-union-juste-incroyable-619ab5b89978e25ff0a2d666 |url-status=live }}</ref> He finished the season as top scorer of the league with 18 goals, and was awarded the Footballer of the Year in Belgium.<ref name="auto"/>

===Brighton & Hove Albion (2022–2023)===
On 31 January 2022, Undav joined [[Premier League]] club [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] for €7 million,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://bx1.be/categories/news/deniz-undav-devient-le-transfert-le-plus-cher-de-lhistoire-de-lunion/|title = Deniz Undav devient le transfert le plus cher de l'histoire de l'Union|date = February 2022}}</ref> signing a four-and-a-half-year deal. He immediately returned to Union Saint-Gilloise until the end of the [[2021–22 Royale Union Saint-Gilloise season|2021–22 season]] on loan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2468362/albion-complete-deal-for-deniz-undav|title=Albion complete deal for Deniz Undav|website=www.brightonandhovealbion.com|date=31 January 2022|access-date=31 January 2022|archive-date=22 May 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240522093553/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/2468362/albion-complete-deal-for-deniz-undav|url-status=dead}}</ref>

Undav made his ''Albion'' debut on the opening game of the [[2022–23 Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. season|2022–23 season]], coming on as a 90+5th minute substitute for [[Danny Welbeck]], helping Brighton win its first ever victory at [[Old Trafford]] after beating [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] 2–1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/blog-the-match/story/4715388/man-united-open-ten-hag-era-with-home-defeat-to-brighton-and-familiar-flaws-on-display|title=Brighton beat Manchester United at Old Trafford for First-Time in Premier League Opening Weekend|date=7 August 2022}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in his second appearance, opening the scoreline in the 3–0 away victory over [[EFL League One|League One]] side [[Forest Green Rovers F.C.|Forest Green Rovers]] in the second round of the [[2022–23 EFL Cup|EFL Cup]] on 24 August.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/24/forest-green-brighton-carabao-cup-match-report|title=Denis Undav opens his goal account as Brighton's youngsters cash in|website=The Guardian|date=24 August 2022|access-date=25 August 2022|archive-date=7 August 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240807114841/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/24/forest-green-brighton-carabao-cup-match-report|url-status=live}}</ref> He didn't score again until over four-and-a-half months later on 7 January 2023, scoring Brighton's last after coming on as a substitute, in the 5–1 away thrashing over [[EFL Championship|Championship]] side [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]] in the [[2022–23 FA Cup#Third round proper|FA Cup]] third round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3012703/five-star-albion-cruise-into-the-fourth-round|title=Five-star Albion cruise into the fourth round|website=Brighton & Hove Albion|date=7 January 2023|access-date=7 January 2023|archive-date=7 January 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230107215557/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3012703/five-star-albion-cruise-into-the-fourth-round|url-status=dead}}</ref> Undav made his first Premier League start on 4 February, creating chances and making several attempts on goal without success before being substituted off in the eventual 1–0 home win over [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|Bournemouth]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 February 2023 |title=More Mitoma magic as Albion leave it late |url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3048710/more-mitoma-magic-as-albion-leave-it-late |access-date=4 February 2023 |website=Brighton & Hove Albion |language=en-GB |archive-date=4 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230204175319/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3048710/more-mitoma-magic-as-albion-leave-it-late |url-status=dead }}</ref> He opened the scoreline on 19 March, scoring a rebound from a [[Moisés Caicedo]] shot, later assisting a [[Evan Ferguson]] goal in the 5–0 FA Cup quarter-final win over [[EFL League Two|League Two]] side [[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3116523/wembley-next-as-albion-cruise-into-fa-cup-semi-finals|title=Wembley next as Albion cruise into FA Cup semi-finals|website=Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|date=19 March 2023|access-date=19 March 2023|archive-date=13 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240413163837/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3116523/wembley-next-as-albion-cruise-into-fa-cup-semi-finals|url-status=dead}}</ref> Undav scored his first Premier League goal on 29 April, opening the scoreline and later adding a second in the 6–0 thrashing of [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolves]], their biggest Premier League victory.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3245199/back-on-track-with-six-of-the-best|title=Back on track with six of the best|publisher=Brighton & Hove Albion|date=29 April 2023|access-date=29 April 2023|archive-date=30 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231130133930/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3245199/back-on-track-with-six-of-the-best|url-status=dead}}</ref> He added to his Premier League tally on 14 May, chipping in ''Albions''' second in the eventual 3–0 away win over [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=It's three and easy as magnificent Albion move up to sixth|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3345249/its-three-and-easy-as-magnificent-albion-move-up-to-sixth|date=14 May 2023|access-date=14 May 2023|website=Brighton & Hove Albion|language=en-GB|archive-date=14 May 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230514180522/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3345249/its-three-and-easy-as-magnificent-albion-move-up-to-sixth|url-status=dead}}</ref> Four days later, Undav scored at both ends in Brighton's 4–1 away defeat at [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle]], heading in an own goal from a corner to open the scoreline before hitting one back from two down.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Late goals make it tough on the Tyne for Albion|url=https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3428662/late-goals-make-it-tough-on-the-tyne-for-albion|date=18 May 2023|access-date=22 May 2023|website=Brighton & Hove Albion|language=en-GB|archive-date=8 November 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241108220031/https://www.brightonandhovealbion.com/news/3428662/late-goals-make-it-tough-on-the-tyne-for-albion|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===VfB Stuttgart (2023–present)===

==== 2023–2024: Initial loan spell ====
On 2 August 2023, Undav returned to his native Germany, signing for [[Bundesliga]] club [[VfB Stuttgart]] on a season-long loan for the [[2023–24 VfB Stuttgart season|2023–24 season]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=VfB sign Deniz Undav |url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2324/undav-/|date=2 August 2023|access-date=2 August 2023|website=VfB Stuttgart}}</ref> He made his Stuttgart debut on 16 September 2023, in a [[Bundesliga]] match against [[1. FSV Mainz 05]]. On 27 January 2024, he scored his first Bundesliga hat-trick in a 5–2 win over [[RB Leipzig]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.de/fussball/bundesliga/2023-2024/vfb-stuttgart-watscht-rb-leipzig-ab-deniz-undav-erzielt-hattrick-erster-pflichtspielsieg-im-neuen-ja_sto9996874/story.shtml |title=VfB Stuttgart watscht RB Leipzig ab: Deniz Undav erzielt Dreierpack - erster Pflichtspielsieg im neuen Jahr |publisher=Eurosport |language=de |date=27 January 2024 |access-date=27 January 2024 |archive-date=27 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240127171749/https://www.eurosport.de/fussball/bundesliga/2023-2024/vfb-stuttgart-watscht-rb-leipzig-ab-deniz-undav-erzielt-hattrick-erster-pflichtspielsieg-im-neuen-ja_sto9996874/story.shtml |url-status=live }}</ref> In his debut Bundesliga season, he scored 18 goals and provided 9 assists, as his club finished second in the league and secured [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] qualification for the first time since 2009–10.<ref>{{cite web |last=Bissett |first=Luke |url=https://www.fotmob.com/topnews/12347-deniz-undavs-dream-debut-season-bundesliga |title=Deniz Undav's dream debut season in the Bundesliga |publisher=FotMob |date=21 May 2024 |access-date=3 June 2024 |archive-date=3 June 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240603191723/https://www.fotmob.com/topnews/12347-deniz-undavs-dream-debut-season-bundesliga |url-status=live }}</ref>

==== 2024–present: Permanent signing and contract extension ====
On 9 August 2024, following a season-long loan spell, Undav signed for VfB Stuttgart on a permanent basis, signing a three-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/neues/profis/2425/deniz-undav-verpflichtung/ |title=VfB verpflichtet Deniz Undav |trans-title=VfB signs Deniz Undav |publisher=VfB Stuttgart |date=9 August 2024 |access-date=9 August 2024 |language=de |archive-date=9 August 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240809114405/https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/aktuell/neues/profis/2425/deniz-undav-verpflichtung/ |url-status=live }}</ref> A month later, on 17 September, he scored a goal on his Champions League debut which ended in a 3–1 away defeat against reigning champions [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/vfb-stuttgarts-deniz-undav-reacts-to-their-3-1-loss-to-real-madrid-we-knew-that-if-we-didnt-score-against-real-we-would-be-punished-40051272 |title=VfB Stuttgart's Deniz Undav reacts to their 3-1 loss to Real Madrid: "We knew that if we didn't score against Real, we would be punished" |publisher=OneFootball |date=18 September 2024 |access-date=27 November 2024 |archive-date=1 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241201222944/https://onefootball.com/en/news/vfb-stuttgarts-deniz-undav-reacts-to-their-3-1-loss-to-real-madrid-we-knew-that-if-we-didnt-score-against-real-we-would-be-punished-40051272 |url-status=live }}</ref>
On 14 February 2026, Undav made his 100th competitive game for Stuttgart, scoring in a 3–1 win over [[1. FC Köln]], his 48th goal for VfB.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.vfb.de/de/vfb/profis/saison/bundesliga/2526/22-vfb-stuttgart----1--fc-koeln-/ |title=VfB Stuttgart – 1.FC Köln |publisher=VfB Stuttgart |access-date=18 February 2026 }}</ref> Later that year, on 9 May, he scored in a 3–1 win over [[Bayer 04 Leverkusen|Bayer Leverkusen]], setting a new personal Bundesliga single-season record with 19 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/goal-scoring-record-and-links-to-kylian-mbappe-vfb-stuttgart-s-deniz-undav-explains-his-special-celebration/bltb9abc43f89a6e2cd |title=Goal-scoring record and links to Kylian Mbappé: VfB Stuttgart's Deniz Undav explains his special celebration |publisher=Goal.com |date=9 May 2026 }}</ref>

On 1 June 2026, VfB Stuttgart announced that Undav extended his contract with the club until June 2029 with an option for another season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2526/verlaengerung-deniz-undav/ |title=VfB extend Deniz Undav deal |publisher=VfB Stuttgart |date=1 June 2026 |access-date=1 June 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Undav was eligible to represent either [[Germany national football team|Germany]] or [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] internationally.<ref>{{cite web | title=Deniz Undav eyes Germany debut and shot at Euro 2024 squad | website=[[Associated Press News]] | date=21 March 2024 | url=https://apnews.com/article/germany-undav-d05fe63d7eed6f1ddfa00ef9e96b8df4 | access-date=23 September 2024 | archive-date=23 September 2024 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240923105033/https://apnews.com/article/germany-undav-d05fe63d7eed6f1ddfa00ef9e96b8df4 | url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Turkey's national team relishing Euro 2024 'home' tournament|last=Sten-Ziemons|first=Andreas|date=18 June 2024|website=[[Deutsche Welle]]|url=https://www.dw.com/en/turkeys-national-team-relishing-euro-2024-home-tournament/a-69398329}}</ref>

In March 2024, aged 27 and having never been capped at youth level, Undav received his first call-up to the German national team ahead of their friendlies against [[France national football team|France]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/start-ins-em-jahr-mit-sechs-neulingen-und-sechs-rueckkehrern-259584/|title=Start ins EM-Jahr mit sechs Neulingen und sechs Rückkehrern|date=14 March 2024|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|access-date=14 March 2024|language=de|archive-date=2 April 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402201335/https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/start-ins-em-jahr-mit-sechs-neulingen-und-sechs-rueckkehrern-259584/|url-status=live}}</ref> He made his debut for ''Die Mannschaft'' in a 2–0 victory against France after coming on for [[Kai Havertz]] in the 80th minute.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/690850/germany-france|title=France v Germany game report|date=23 March 2024|access-date=24 March 2024|archive-date=24 March 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240324164800/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/690850/germany-france|url-status=live}}</ref> Undav was named in Germany's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://olympics.com/en/news/uefa-euro-2024-all-squads-and-players-full-list|title=UEFA Euro 2024: All squads and players full list|date=7 June 2024|access-date=7 June 2024|website=Olympics.com|archive-date=8 June 2024|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240608183748/https://olympics.com/en/news/uefa-euro-2024-all-squads-and-players-full-list|url-status=live}}</ref> Undav scored his first international goal in a 2–2 draw against the Netherlands on 10 September 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-09-10 |title=Undav "over the moon" after scoring his first goal for Germany |url=https://bulinews.com/undav-over-the-moon-after-scoring-his-first-goal-for-germany |access-date=2024-10-26 |website=Bundesliga News in English |language=en |archive-date=8 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241108220654/https://bulinews.com/undav-over-the-moon-after-scoring-his-first-goal-for-germany |url-status=live }}</ref> He was named to Germany's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026 World Cup]].<ref>https://www.tagesschau.de/sport/wm-kader-neuer-100.html</ref>

==Personal life==
Undav was born in Germany to [[Kurds|Kurdish]]-[[Yazidi]] parents from the village of [[Işıklı, Viranşehir|Işıklı]], located within the municipality of [[Viranşehir]] and situated in [[Şanlıurfa Province]] of Turkey. He is one of five children. His grandfather migrated to Germany due to pressure following the [[1980 Turkish coup d'état|1980 coup in Turkey]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.voetbalprimeur.be/nieuws/923765/officieel-corona-houdt-union-niet-tegen-duitse-topschutter-zet-handtekening.html|title=OFFICIEEL: Union denkt toch al vooruit en trekt topschutter uit Duitsland aan|website=www.voetbalprimeur.be|date=7 April 2020|access-date=8 June 2020|archive-date=2 December 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202035513/https://www.voetbalprimeur.be/nieuws/923765/officieel-corona-houdt-union-niet-tegen-duitse-topschutter-zet-handtekening.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Diyarbakır Karacadağ'dan Alman Milli Takımına uzandı |url=https://www.cermikgazetesi.com/diyarbakir-karacadagdan-alman-milli-takimina-uzandi |access-date=2024-03-24 |website=CEGA Medya - Diyarbakır Son Dakika Haberleri |language=tr |archive-date=8 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241208022237/https://www.cermikgazetesi.com/diyarbakir-karacadagdan-alman-milli-takimina-uzandi |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=DENİZ UNDAV'IN KUZENİ KONUŞTU: O Kürtlerin Maradonası |url=https://www.guneydoguekspres.com/deniz-undavin-kuzeni-konustu-o-kurtlerin-maradonasi |access-date=2024-03-24 |website=Ekspres Haber - Sondakika Diyarbakır ve Bölge haberleri |language=tr |archive-date=24 March 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240324171422/https://www.guneydoguekspres.com/deniz-undavin-kuzeni-konustu-o-kurtlerin-maradonasi |url-status=live }}</ref>

